I also don't think that co-processor in a cartridge is a really good idea. It would be not much of NES there - if you want more processing power, there are lots of other platforms, why not just code for N64 or something?; NES is not that limited in CPU power anyway, not as much as it limited with, say, spirites per scanline; it is also not emulated - debug problems.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4205">Shiru</a> — Wed Feb 08, 2012 12:59 pm</p><hr />
